projects.name: ELECTIVE BUCKET SELECTION
projects.description: Developed an Elective Bucket Selection website facilitating student enrollment for elective courses based on their quiz scores. Utilized PHP, HTML, SQL, and other relevant technologies to create an intuitive platform enabling seamless selection and allocation of elective buckets.

projects.name: SENTIMENT ANALYSIS
projects.description: Developed a robust machine learning model to classify customer sentiments as positive or negative. Utilized Python libraries such as NLTK, scikitlearn, and TensorFlow for text preprocessing and model training. Implemented feature engineering and selection methods to enhance model accuracy and performance.

projects.name: JAVA PROJECT
projects.description: Comprehensive Backend Development: Developed a robust tour and travel application using Java, incorporating Spring Boot for microservices architecture, Hibernate for ORM, and MySQL for database management. FullStack Implementation: Implemented RESTful web services for seamless client-server communication and integrated frontend interfaces using JSP and Servlets for dynamic content delivery. Maintainable Codebase: Employed Maven for project build management, JUnit for unit testing, and followed best practices in object-oriented programming (OOP) to ensure a scalable and maintainable codebase.
